                            <comment id="15215486" author="gurwls223" created="Tue, 29 Mar 2016 05:49:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=rxin&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;rxin&quot;&gt;rxin&lt;/a&gt; I can work on this but would you maybe confirm whether this should be inferred as &lt;tt&gt;StringType&lt;/tt&gt; or &lt;tt&gt;DoubleType&lt;/tt&gt; in this case? To be permissive, this might have to be &lt;tt&gt;DoubleType&lt;/tt&gt; but users would think this is weird if it has &lt;tt&gt;DoubleType&lt;/tt&gt; with &lt;tt&gt;floatAsBigDecimal&lt;/tt&gt; enabled.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15215497" author="rxin" created="Tue, 29 Mar 2016 06:01:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I am not sure what the right behavior is actually.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;one thing I noticed: floatAsBigDecimal -&amp;gt; prefersDecimal &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think this is a better option name?&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Can we just trim the floating point number if it doesn&apos;t fit in a decimal?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15215560" author="gurwls223" created="Tue, 29 Mar 2016 06:51:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I will change the name when I open a PR and yes I think we can do.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Can I try to open a PR based on this idea?&lt;/p&gt;

</comment>
                            <comment id="15215563" author="rxin" created="Tue, 29 Mar 2016 06:52:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes - if it works.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15215577" author="gurwls223" created="Tue, 29 Mar 2016 06:58:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry for adding many comment but maybe would this better just infers them as &lt;tt&gt;DoubleType&lt;/tt&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I just noticed JSON data source produces &lt;tt&gt;DoubleType&lt;/tt&gt; when it does not fix in a decimal during trying to find a compatible type.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If &lt;tt&gt;prefersDecimal&lt;/tt&gt; does not infer all floating types must be &lt;tt&gt;DecimalTypes&lt;/tt&gt; then, I feel it might be okay to make this &lt;tt&gt;DoubleType&lt;/tt&gt; when it does not fit.. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15215579" author="rxin" created="Tue, 29 Mar 2016 07:00:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yea that works too. I think we really just need to be clear in our definition. If we do double, we should update the documentation and say this only works if the data can fit in a decimal.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15215673" author="apachespark" created="Tue, 29 Mar 2016 08:25:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;User &apos;HyukjinKwon&apos; has created a pull request for this issue:&lt;br/&gt;
